    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, really? i feel like i hear the exact opposite all the time. like, isn't the main argument that if people get more benefits, they'll just decide it's not worth it to get a job? i thought most people said it creates a \"welfare trap\" where you actually lose money if you start working. shouldn't there be more debate on that side though?",
