      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The notion that the social safety net creates a \"welfare trap\" is a myth perpetuated by conservative politicians and think tanks. The evidence shows that the vast majority of people who receive benefits are not deterred from working by the prospect of losing them. In fact, many low-income individuals and families rely on the social safety net as a temporary safety net while they're looking for work or rebuilding their lives. The idea that people are more likely to work if they're not eligible for benefits is simply not supported by the data.",
